questions.content:
After drilling, a well passport is issued that includes all technical data related to the well:
• Location;
• Drilling rig type and model;
• Well structure (drilling, casing/filter diameters and intervals, pump model, capacity, and installation depth);
• Aquifer characteristics (static and dynamic levels, yield, filtration coefficient, transmissivity, and radius of influence);
• Recommendations (general and specific) for optimal operation.

The well passport is essential for proper operation and future rehabilitation, if needed.
